    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Until the spell ends, freezing rain and sleet fall in a 20-foot-tall cylinder with a 40-foot radius centered on a point you choose within range. The area is &amp;Reference[rule=heavilyobscured]{heavily obscured}, and exposed flames in the area are doused.</p><p>The ground in the area is covered with slick ice, making it &amp;Reference[rule=difficultterrain]{difficult terrain}. When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, it falls &amp;Reference[condition=prone].</p><p>If a creature starts its turn in the spell's area and is @status[concentration||concentrating] on a spell, the creature must make a successful Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC or lose @status[concentration].</p></div>",
